# Experiment variants (toolbar A / B / C / D)

- **Shared UI:** normal JSX — visible in every experiment.
- **One variant only:** wrap in `ExperimentGate` from `components/ExperimentGate.tsx` with `experimentId` from props and `variants={['a']}`, `variants={['b']}`, `variants={['c','d']}`, etc. as needed.
- **CSS-only for one variant:** use `body.proto-experiment-a` / `body.proto-experiment-b` / `body.proto-experiment-c` / `body.proto-experiment-d` in `index.css`, not unscoped Tailwind in shared components.

- **Home leaderboard tabs:** cohort pills come from `getHomeLeaderboardCohortTabs(experimentId)` in `homeLeaderboardSprint1Data.ts` (`HOME_LEADERBOARD_COHORT_TABS_A` vs `_B` for **b**, **c**, and **d**). Edit only the list for the experiment you mean to change.

- **Home leaderboard B/C/D:** **B/C** use `HomeLeaderboardExperimentB` + `homeLeaderboardExperimentBData`. **D** uses `HomeLeaderboardExperimentD` (Figma 278:4639 promo + **Around you** preview on the right) until unlock, then reuses B’s unlocked UI. Helpers `isHomeLeaderboardExperimentBCard`, `usesWiderHomeLeaderboardCohortTabs`, and `isHomeLeaderboardBlurGateExperiment` live in `homeLeaderboardGate.ts`. Unlock when `m1-l1`–`m1-l5` are completed (`areHomeLeaderboardUnlockLessonsComplete`). **B** hides the card until unlock. **C** blurs the grid until unlock with a minimal title-only header. **D** shows the promo until unlock.

When changing other `Home` / `HomeLeaderboard` markup, use `ExperimentGate` or scoped CSS so B/C/D-only work does not appear in A unless intentional.
